  "body": "## Issue\r\nA specifically encountered error:\r\n\r\n>openzeppelin-solidity/contracts/MaskedContract.sol:1:1: SyntaxError: Source file requires different compiler version (current compiler is 0.4.25+commit.59dbf8f1.Emscripten.clang - note that nightly builds are considered to be strictly less than the released version\r\npragma solidity ^0.5.0;\r\n^---------------------^\r\nCompilation failed. See above.\r\nTruffle v5.0.7 (core: 5.0.7)\r\nNode v9.3.0\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\nHave a (possibly old) configuration setting that includes the following, in the config file:\r\n```\r\n  compilers: {\r\n    solc: {\r\n      version: \"^0.4.22\"\r\n    }\r\n  },\r\n```\r\nand have a smart contract which uses a `pragma solidity ^0.5.0`.\r\nNote that the \"current compiler is 0.4.25\" being different from the config \"0.4.22\" might be slightly confusing in the error message, but valid.\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\nAn error message that gets me closer to fixing the problem, maybe including a sentence like:\r\n\"Your truffle config specifies solc version ^0.4.22. See https://truffleframework.com/docs/truffle/reference/configuration#compiler-configuration for more information about how to specify a compiler version.\"\r\nThis would appear when Truffle catches an error with \"Source file requires different compiler version,\" in addition to the existing text.  The first new sentence would only appear if a compiler version was actually specified in the config.\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: Windows 10 Pro\r\n* Ethereum client: N/A\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): 5.0.7\r\n* node version (`node --version`): 9.3.0\r\n* npm version (`npm --version`): 6.9.0\r\n",
